\h EQUIPMENT \d

\uUSAGE\n
equipment \s[\ditem \s...]\d

\uDESCRIPTION\n
Display your readied equipment, or examine one or more items in your readied equipment.

\uEXAMPLES\n
\qequipment\d to get a list of the items you have readied.4`
\qequipment sword\d to examine the sword you are wielding.4`
\qequipment sword boots\d to examine the sword you are wielding and the boots you are wearing.4`
\qequipment \p2#i\qnecklace\d to examine the second necklace you are wearing.4`
\qequipment \p2#m\qring\d to examine the first two rings you are wearing.4`
\qequipment \p3#i\qring \p3#m\qbracelet\d to examine the third ring and the first three bracelets you are wearing.4`
\qequipment \p#a\qring\d to examine all of the rings you are wearing.4`
\qequipment \p#a\d to examine everything you have readied.4`

\uSEE ALSO\n
abbreviation, inventory, look, prefixes
